name: Modern 2 bedroom apartment in HK!
summary: Welcome to our Hong Kong home! My husband and I live in a 2 bedroom apartment with our cat, Dusty, in the heart of Wan Chai on HK island.  We live in a great location with a wide range of local and western restaurants near by. 5-7 minute walk to MTR.
space: My husband and I live in a 2 bedroom apartment in Wan Chai - the heart of Hong Kong. We live on the 7th floor and have minimal road noise. We have Wellcome Supermarket downstairs (30 second walk), numerous coffee shops within a 3 minute walk and we live 2 minutes away from the restaurant district - Ship, Star, Sun and Moon street. You will find numerous international cuisines only a stones throw away! Wan Chai is the place to be when visiting Hong Kong!  We adopted an 18 year old cat called Dusty about 18 months ago and he is an incredibly sweet cat. You will not even notice he is there. He is an indoor cat and uses a litter tray that would need to be emptied (just in the corridor bin) if you were staying for longer than 4 days. He eats twice a day but we are happy for you to feed him two meals at one time (using the extra dish) if that suits you best. He is very low maintenance and sleeps for around 20 hours a day!

neighborhood_overview: Happy Valley is an up-market residential neighbourhood that is 5 minutes from Causeway Bay.  The horse-racing course is also of walking distance from the Lofts and guests can enjoy Wednesday Night Races (sometimes Sundays), a must-do Hong Kong activity.  The neighbourhood streets are lined with quaint cafés (Chinese and Western) and boutiques, a variety of international restaurants and massage places.
notes: Loft is on the Third floor.  Please note that there is no elevator, but it is an easy walk upstairs.  Loft is 68 Steps up from Street Level. *Airbnb Verified Photos - Rest assured that the place is as it is portrayed in the photos as you can see some photos in the Loft 2 gallery are taken by an official Airbnb Photographer.  (All units are exactly the same)
transit: There are a variety of public transport available from the Lofts including the Bus, Minibus and Taxis.  Within one block is the tram station that can take you anywhere along the harbour on the island.  Causeway Bay is 5 minutes away by car where the MTR (Subway) network is available linking most of Hong Kong.
access: Guests will be issued an access card that opens the main door from the street as well as their loft.   There is a communal roof with a barbecue grill and space for entertaining.
interaction: We are always available to help you with any recommendations or if you have any transportation needs.  We can help you book airport transfers for up to 4 passengers at HK350 / Way, HK450 for pick ups between midnight at 7am.
house_rules: Unfortunately Smoking is not permitted, but should you wish, you may smoke on the roof terrace or down on the street.  Pets are also not permitted unless special permission has been granted.
host_about:
I love to travel (60+ Countries and counting) and when I do, I like to live like a local, yet come home every night to all the amenities I am used to.  

That's why I created KELLY LOFTS.  A unique space in an upmarket residential neighborhood, with all the luxuries of a 5-star Hotel, but with the privacy and feel of your own home.   This is how you can really feel what it's really like to live in Hong Kong, without all the hassles of dealing with the small details.

Feel free to hit me up for recommendations or things to do.  I have a pretty wide range of suggestions from exclusive Michelin eats to roadside local experiences.  I also like to think I'm quite connected and up-to-date with what's going on locally, so I'm pretty sure I can get you what you need.  

Enjoy your travels!

neighborhood_overview: Causeway Bay (Chinese: 銅鑼灣) is a heavily built-up area of Hong Kong, located on Hong Kong Island, and covering parts of Wan Chai and Eastern districts. The Chinese name is also romanized as Tung Lo Wan as in Tung Lo Wan Road (銅鑼灣道). The rent in the shopping areas of Causeway Bay was ranked as the world's most expensive for the second year in a row, after overtaking New York's Fifth Avenue in 2012. Causeway Bay or East Point is one of Hong Kong's major shopping districts. It includes the 13-storey Japanese department store Sogo, Times Square, an indoor shopping complex, and Hysan Place. There are also smaller malls such as World Trade Centre, Windsor House, Hang Lung Centre, Fashion Island, Fashion Walk, Lee Gardens and Lee Gardens Two. Causeway Bay is one of the most crowded areas in Hong Kong since it contains many trendy shops carrying both locally made fashion and products from Japan, Europe and the United States. neighborhood_overview: This enigmatic city of skyscrapers, ancient traditions and heavenly food will fascinate, whether it's your first visit or your 50th. Culture Beyond the glass and steel of Hong Kong’s commercial persona, the city also boasts a vibrant cultural scene that features the eclectic influences of its Chinese roots, colonial connections and a wondrous pool of homegrown talent. Here, you’re just as likely to find yourself applauding at Asia’s top film festival as joining in dawn taichi or reading the couplets of a local poet to the drumbeat of a dragon boat. Culture could also mean indie music under the stars, a classy art walk, your first Cantonese opera – not to mention the exhibitions and events staged year-round at the many museums and concert halls. Why I Love Hong Kong I love Hong Kong because it has a complexity that eludes definition, sometimes even by its own people. I can be soul-searching near the Chinese border, lunching with Sikhs at a Sikh temple, splurging on a set of kitchen kniv
notes: Please note that not every neighbor is happy about the New Sharing Economy. If we want them to understand the 21st century :-)) we should respect normal house rules like.... no party after 10pm, be quiet in the staircase/hallway, don't ring at neighbours bell because you cannot find the key in your handbag, don't throw things out of the window, eg. Just use your common sense.  Although the apartment is on a very high standard and equipped like a serviced apartment - I am still a private host but not a Hotel with fully employed staff and a front desk. Me and my team are always happy to assist - but if can take time to follow your not urgent request (like 1 more towel).
transit: By ferry The Kowloon waterfront at Tsim Sha Tsui Riding the Star Ferry from Central or Wan Chai ferry piers is considered a "must-do" for any traveller to Hong Kong. Not only is this the cheapest way to traverse the harbour, it's also the finest way to go sight-seeing, particularly at night, where you're surrounded by a wall of lights and skyscrapers on both sides. If you're feeling posh, you can pay fractionally more and travel as an upper-deck passenger. Alternatively, you can travel steerage and maybe get a glimpse into the noisy engine room. By train The Airport Express takes you to Kowloon MTR station in just 20 minutes. Most of Hong Kong's rail lines converge on Kowloon. If you are travelling from Hong Kong island, change at Admirality on the Island Line for the MTR to Tsim Sha Tsui from Hong Kong island. The MTR to Tsim Sha Tsui offers a faster service and is the most popular choice for commuters, so avoid Admiralty interchange during the rush hour (5 PM to 7 PM). Alternatively

By walking 5 minutes from the hotel, you can find public bus stops lead to each area of Hong Kong, airport A21 Bus Station ( in downstairs of the hotel, only walk 5 seconds you can reach it), and hundreds of snack stores, shops, and currency exchange shop. Many famous stores such as SaSa, Bonjour, Fortress, Broadway, Chow Sang Sang, Chow Tai Fook, Milan Station (mainly sell big brand bags) are also at nearby, and it is only 120m away from the largest Shopping Mall Langham Place at Mongkok. As long as the calendar show that the room is in “green” status, it means the room can be booked, you can make reservation directly. We can 100% ensure the room is vacant. house_rules: *我們的房間一旦確認訂單,即不接受變更改期。只能根據退訂政策執行退訂。 * 請帶好您的有效身份證件辦理入住。我們的房間由於硬件性的分布在大廈不同樓層,所以我們的房間不支持選房選樓層入住,預訂成功後分配入住的房間所在樓層及房號以賓館安排為準。  * 香港住宿價格浮動頻繁,我們亦不例外。價格以預訂付款時的價格為準,付款預訂之後價格上漲不會再追加房費;價格下跌我們亦不會退還差價;訂單付款後,如您的行程有变化請在入住前20天郵件聯系告知我們。入住期間有任何問題必須及時聯系我们協調,不聯系擅自離去的,房間空置房費照收.  * 房間嚴格根據相應房型限住人數限定入住,超過人數我們有權利额外加收100HKD/人/天的費用或拒絕入住;入住時間為14:00,退房時間為次日中午12:00;如超過中午12點未辦理好退房手續需要額外加收100元HKD/小時的房費。并且如果已经到了中午12:00,如果客人既没办理退房,也不在所住房间内,我们有权将客人放在房间内的所有物品存放在一个安全的地方,使房间可以由下一位客人使用。我們的初衷並非為了高價賺取超時費用,而是為了能及時做好房間清潔不耽誤下一位顧客能準時入住。 *入住當天提前到達或退房後均可免費寄存行李。退房後行李寄存時限為退房當天的晚上18:00之前. 行李寄存服务时间为早上9:30-下午18:00,如果您的到達時間早於服务時間可以先去吃早餐之後再到達賓館辦理寄存。如果您寄存行李需要寄存超過退房當天18:00,需要額外加收費50HKD每6小時的寄存費用。不足6小時按6小時收費。 * 請在入住期間愛護房內配備設施,有意或無意弄污床上用品、損壞房間內設施須在入住押金內照價賠償。貴重物品請自己隨身攜帶保管好,對我們雖然要對客人盡職盡責,可我們不會以任何方式負責客人的物品或其他財產的損失。 *在您計畫离开房間出門之前,確保房間內所有水龙头,及電源(電燈、空調等)處於關閉狀態,讓我們可以環保的持續提供有價格競爭力的房間給大家。 *晚上10點後噪音水平必須保持在最低限度,以免打擾或造成滋擾鄰居或其他房間的客人。 * 請勿將房間用於違法活動。 禁止攜帶寵物入住。 下訂單付款即視為認同本規則,如果不認同,請在下訂單付款之前慎重的三思考慮。
host_about: 我是helen,本着以客为尊的服务原则,为来香港公干,自由行旅游的客人提供方便,舒适平价实惠的住宿.一直以来我都有在其他平台上做香港宾馆预订,得到众多的好评.通过朋友介绍,得知“Airbnb”这个住宿预订服务平台.我就加入了Airbnb的大家庭.这里是一个真正为房东和房客服务的平台.希望各位房客能多多关注我的房间.谢谢支持!我经营的全为每间房间都有独卫,每天都有专人打扫,用品一客一换的套房,竭力为每位来客提供便利舒适的入住环境。你们的评价是我们服务的动力,有了你们的支持和建议我们才能做得更好~

我来自北京,住在香港20年,所以香港现在是我的家,我愛香港。想邀請你去體驗香港的生活。

香港是繁華的國際化的都市,著名的動感之都,美稱東方之珠。HAWAII KELLY HOSTEL是位於東方之珠的中心尖沙咀的中心地帶,在這個繁華的都市寸土寸金的尖沙咀的中心。HAWAII KELLY HOSTEL房間雖小但是精細,它以經濟舒適,清潔整齊,交通方便為主,是賓客的最佳選擇,希望給各位賓客有家的感覺

溫馨提示:HAWAII KELLYHOSTEL房間雖小但是精細,它以經濟舒適,清潔整齊,交通方便為主,是民宿,賓館

5星的酒店豪華 房間大,如:半島酒店,香格裡拉酒店。但是5星的酒店是民宿,賓館10倍的價錢。

name: Window onto the world - 2pp Studio
summary: Cosy and convenient studio with a splendid view of the city. Right on top of the metro, in an area rich with markets, restaurants and niche shopkeepers. A quiet place to come home to after a night on the town, ideal for romantic getaways.
space: The studio is fully equipped with all the amenities to accommodate both short and long-term stays. There's a comfortable queen-sized bed to encourage you to sleep in. The bathroom is clean and has dressing room style lighting around the mirror. But the view is what really makes this flat unique. Most Hong Kong listings have small windows or aren't high up enough to provide an open panoramic view. Here you'll see the Kowloon mountain range on your left, you'll look down onto the bustling Mong Kok streets in the middle, and you'll find the skylines of both Hong Kong and the Kowloon Peninsula on your right. You're also more than welcome to cook in the flat, though you'd be missing out on the fantastic little restaurants that make Prince Edward a fabulous place to live.

neighborhood_overview: Neighbourhood Goldfish Street, Fa Yuen Street Market, and the Flower Market are the neighbourhood attractions you'll find in your guide book. What's really special here are the alleys and walkways which connect them. Hong Kong is extremely dense, so the more niche shops have had to move to the second or third floors in walk-up buildings. That's where you'll find your python liquors and goggle-eyed camera repairmen. ☆☆ Rich in markets and local cuisine ☆☆ The cultural richness cuts across time and makes Prince Edward a trendy neighbourhood which keeps its traditional charm while skyscrapers are popping up everywhere. It's amazing just how many good Dim Sum (typical Cantonese dishes) restaurants are still around. There's even two Michelin starred restaurants within walking distance!
notes: Flat Entertainment  For the rainy days we have curated a selection of the finest works in Hong Kong cinema. Available upon request.  For longer stays you might want to switch things up a little. We have an extensive two-player board game collection. Available upon request.
transit: Getting Around Proximity to the MTR is everything in Hong Kong as trains depart every other minute and will take you to most places in under twenty. The Prince Edward MTR entrance is just outside our building, with the following travel times to popular destinations: ☆☆ On top of the metro, very well connected ☆☆ * Mong Kok (1 min) * Sham Shui Po (2 min) * Tsim Sha Tsui (10 min) * Central (15 min) * Wan Chai (15 min) * Causeway Bay (18 min) At night a taxi will take you back from popular nightlife hotspots LKF, Wan Chai, Knutsford terrace within 15 minutes and under HK 100. Prince Edward is also adjacent to the transportation hub of Mong Kok, so even when you're trying to get to the more remote temples and sights, there's literally no place in Hong Kong that isn't served by a bus or train from here.  A21 Bus HK 38 // Taxi HK 250   Airport arrivals are painless as the A21 Airport bus (50 minutes) stops just 250 meters from our place. A taxi would get you there in 30 minutes. In both
access: Amenities Anything in the house has been left there for your convenience. So please feel free to use the bathing products, take the guide books on your day out, and fire up the entertainment system for your leisure. ☆☆ Please use the space like it's your own! ☆☆ There's a wardrobe for your clothes, coffee and tea, fresh towels, and the kitchen is equipped to prepare simple meals.
interaction: Concierge I'm really keen to make your stay as convenient and enjoyable as possible. So even though you have the whole flat to yourself, I'll be staying just around the corner. If there is anything I can assist you with during your stay, I'm always just a buzz away! As you might have gathered from my reviews, I love chatting about the latest and greatest developments here, so I should be able to loop you into what's happening around town.
house_rules: House Rules We want you to feel at home and treat the apartment the same way you'd treat your own. We hope you'll feel comfortable with the following: * For the safety of your belongings, be sure to pull the door into the lock after passing in or out of the flat. * When leaving the apartment, please switch off the AC and lights. * No smoking indoors. There is a landscaped outdoor area on the second floor which doubles as the building's smoker hangout. * Please restrict pet action to the Gold Fish market downstairs.
host_about: Apophenic without a cause.

neighborhood_overview: I love to continually learn about the history of HK which I find fascinating.  Hollywood Road was the first road to be completed in HK in 1844 and the road and streets off it are full of history.  I find that so many of the people, both local and expats are incredibly busy here rushing around so don't always have their eyes fully open.  As a tourist you have time to appreciate the area fully.  Pak Tsz Lane Park is very close by just off Hollywood Rd and is one my favourite little places tucked away. Man Mo Temple and Aesop Park are further down Hollywood Road towards Sheung Wan.  I have a book on the shelf for historical walks in the area for anybody to look at if interested.  Whatever you are looking for in HK it's on your doorstep here and it's a great area to walk around.
notes: You have all the bars and restaurant's of Soho on your doorstep and LKF is 200m away but the flat is surprisingly quiet.  The bathroom in the flat is very small as it's an old building. There is a small open kitchen.  The flat is a 4th floor walk up in case you have an aversion to stairs.
transit: You can get a taxi outside of the flat easily.  There's also the escalator/walkway across the road which leads down to the IFC mall and the MTR is just 5 mins away.
interaction: If I'm in HK I interact as much as I can or as much as the guest prefers.
house_rules: No smoking.  No pets.  Treat the place with respect.
host_about: I'm originally from Manchester in the UK and have traveled for most of my life and can't seem to stop.  I've based myself in HK since 2008 and I split my time between there and time on the road.

neighborhood_overview: Central (also Central District; Chinese: 中環) is the central business district of Hong Kong. It is located in Central and Western District, on the north shore of Hong Kong Island, across Victoria Harbour from Tsim Sha Tsui, the southernmost point of Kowloon Peninsula. The area was the heart of Victoria City, although that name is rarely used today. As the central business district of Hong Kong, it is the area where many multinational financial services corporations have their headquarters. Consulates general and consulates of many countries are also located in this area, as is Government Hill, the site of the government headquarters. The area, with its proximity to Victoria Harbour, has served as the centre of trade and financial activities from the earliest days of the British colonial era in 1841, and continues to flourish and serve as the place of administration after the transfer of sovereignty to China in 1997. neighborhood_overview: When it comes to finding the best of Hong Kong's nightlife, there's one rule: go west. This has been true since the days when Lan Kwai Fong was an edgy alternative to Wan Chai, and even cooler types spent their time at warehouse parties in Western district godowns. Then came the more laid-back restaurant-and-bar scene of SoHo, which has steadily bled west as rents have risen. That's where Sai Ying Pun comes in. Though it has been a low-key residential neighbourhood for decades, its origins were much rowdier. First settled by the British military (its name literally means "West Camp"), the compact street grid was laid down in the 1880s and soon filled up with crowded tenements, brothels and opium dens. The red-light district proved short lived — by 1900, the bawdy houses had migrated west, to Shek Tong Tsui. If you need a local SIM card, there is a 7-11 in the middle section  of the main arrival hall where they see all types of SIM cards, I usually prefer the PCCW brand as it is the larges local operator.

neighborhood_overview: Causeway Bay (Chinese: 銅鑼灣) is a heavily built-up area of Hong Kong, located on Hong Kong Island, and covering parts of Wan Chai and Eastern districts. The Chinese name is also romanized as Tung Lo Wan as in Tung Lo Wan Road (銅鑼灣道). The rent in the shopping areas of Causeway Bay was ranked as the world's most expensive for the second year in a row, after overtaking New York's Fifth Avenue in 2012. Causeway Bay or East Point is one of Hong Kong's major shopping districts. It includes the 13-storey Japanese department store Sogo, Times Square, an indoor shopping complex, and Hysan Place. There are also smaller malls such as World Trade Centre, Windsor House, Hang Lung Centre, Fashion Island, Fashion Walk, Lee Gardens and Lee Gardens Two. Causeway Bay is one of the most crowded areas in Hong Kong since it contains many trendy shops carrying both locally made fashion and products from Japan, Europe and the United States. As such, it is a popular social spot for young people. Many shops are

Check Inn HK, a place you could call it home.

neighborhood_overview: This neighbourhood is an absolute treasure as it it hidden away from the hustle and bustle and it is only a corner away from everything that you may want to dive into while staying in HK. I can definitely share some of my favourite spots in this very cool and upcoming place to be. The list is endless from bakeries and coffee shops to any kind of restaurant you can possibly think of. Hopewell Centre is a good place to start (just a 5 minute walk), you can find the local supermarket here as well as the HSBC bank and even a Starbucks coffee if you wish. Our neighborhood is also known for its exercise routes (Bowen Road) which can be accessed from our road.
notes: My main goal is for you to have a very easy and pleasant experience in this wonderful city. I really think you'll love it as much as I do :)
transit: Public transportation in HK is very accessible. Just down the hill (3 minute walk) you can access a taxi. The prices may range from 30 Hong Kong Dollars upwards. Cheaper options include the bus, tram or the MTR ( metro train). They are all very close and in walking distance from the apartment (5-8 minutes walking distance). I look forward to hearing from you and meeting you. Wishing you nothing but happy adventures in Hong Kong.

The horse-racing course is also of walking distance from the Lofts and guests can enjoy Wednesday Night Races (sometimes Sundays), a must-do Hong Kong activity.  The neighbourhood streets are lined with quaint cafés (Chinese and Western) and boutiques, a variety of international restaurants and massage places.

host_about:
I love to travel (60+ Countries and counting) and when I do, I like to live like a local, yet come home every night to all the amenities I am used to.  

That's why I created KELLY LOFTS.  A unique space in an upmarket residential neighborhood, with all the luxuries of a 5-star Hotel, but with the privacy and feel of your own home.   This is how you can really feel what it's really like to live in Hong Kong, without all the hassles of dealing with the small details.

Feel free to hit me up for recommendations or things to do.  I have a pretty wide range of suggestions from exclusive Michelin eats to roadside local experiences.  I also like to think I'm quite connected and up-to-date with what's going on locally, so I'm pretty sure I can get you what you need.  

Enjoy your travels!

neighborhood_overview: Bottom Line - If you want to stay central but not city central, in a more traditional and up & coming area with great amenities and transport links then BOOK! Causeway Bay (Tin Hau) - this old HK district is set/based around Electric Road which is the arterial road with all life in and around it. The area is currently going through radical redevelopment on both property and social fronts which has attracted the attention of local and international professionals and young families desperate for living space in this area. This influx of people and money has resulted in new cool bars, bistros, restaurants, independent businesses etc. opening up to compliment the well established local businesses that have been trading here for years and still thriving today. This collaboration of “old meets new” in this funky neighbourhood has created a new unique experience not to be missed. Whether you decide to stay with me or not definitely put Causway Bay Tin Hau/Tai Hang on your itinerary so you can
notes: Cleaning of the apartment is included the price and  you can arrange directly with my help for her to do your laundry  - 100 HKD for full load wash, dry, iron and hang up.*you must giver her notice.
transit: You are smack bang in the middle of Causeway Bay (Tin Hau, Electric Road) and have MTR links (AKA Metro/Tube)  5 mins walk from my front door where you find full access to the MTR system for HK and Kowloon. The main bus stop with buses to everywhere on the island is on my street and left of the main entrance. The Taxis congregate right outside the apartment complex or on the main road (Whitfield and Electric Road).
access: You will either meet me or my helper to get keys and main door access code. Not that they will ask or care however, as far as any doormen/neighbours concerned you are my friends visiting :-)
interaction: When I'm around and mood/schedule dependent i'll be as involved or elusive as you like i.e. we could be passing ships in the night, boozy and laughing on the terrace, chilling with a movie and take away or poss out on the town if we so wish. lets just take it as it comes with no commitments or expectations. Cecile is my helper. She works 8am-7pm Mon-Fri and ½ day Saturday and lives out of the apartment. Essentially she is there to look after Albert and the household upkeep while I’m at work or out playing so she will sporadically pop in and out throughout the day to clean the whole apartment, walk the dog, laundry etc Albert is my 6 year old  Beaglier (cross Beagle/Cavalier) which means he is very intelligent (Beagle) and very charming (Cavalier). The house is his domain however keep your room door shut when you leave to avoid any kleptomania (he has form lol). Finally, never feed him, oh, and do expect to be randomly sniffed, licked and harassed to play fetch!
house_rules: Don't feed Albert (my dog) but pat and play with him :-) Always press the lock on the main entrance interior door when you leave. No smoking in the house but on either terrace is absolutely fine* no cigarettes to be thrown over the side, please use ash tray provided. No random overnight guests *willing to discuss up front if you have friends in town who want to visit on a case by case basis. The helper Cecile is employed by me and I’m happy to discuss how/where/when she can help you however direction/instruction must come from me except if you want her to do laundry and you just arrange with her directly. Anything else can be discussed and agreed before booking.
host_about:
I’m from Scotland originally however I have been lucky enough to have lived/traveled and worked all round the world for the last 20 years. During this time I spent 8 years in Europe working summers/winters as resort manager so have a pretty good grasp on hosting inquisitive travelers from around the globe as well as comfortable making my own way in new and exciting places.

Since Jan 2011 I have been living, working, hiking, eating, drinking and touring around Hong Kong. I love this rock and all the exciting things it offers and I’m happy to share my experiences, the good, bad, ugly and funny!

Up to 18 square meter ,Furnished with designer décor and modern lighting, these rooms provide a real home away from home after a long day of work or discovery of the city.  Guests can have choices of one double bed (16 square meter) or two single beds (18 square meter).

4-beds Room without window
Up to 16 square meter ,Equipped with 2 bunk bed, these rooms make family travel a much more affordable one.

Family Room
Up to 22 square meter ,Equipped with a double bed and a bunk bed, these rooms make family travel a much more affordable one.

Pandora Suite
Up to 30 square meter ,Each Pandora Suite comprises of a living room with sofa and TV set, and a bedroom equipped with double bed and a bunk bed.  These rooms can comfortably accommodate a family of four.

Executive Room
Up to 26 square meter ,These rooms are elegantly designed to meet the requirements of both business and leisure travellers.  They are perfect for those guests who are looking for high quality of standards in a more spacious room.
the quickest way from the airport to our serviced hotel would be taking airport express to Kowloon station (around hkd90 per head, 25 mins) and change Taxi (around hkd25-30) to our hotel (Buckingham building). 
alternatively , the most economical way is to take shuttle bus A22 and get off at 4th stop, Chi Wo Street, Jordan Road   (around hkd40 per head, one hour)
From Exit A, Jordan station, turn left and take the first left (don't cross to the opposite side of nathan road!) , walk down one block and we are next to Luk Fok Jewelry, hotel located inside Buckingham Building 9th floor.

summary: This large studio in the heart of Soho has everything you need for you stay in Hong Kong. Next to the Central escalator,  it's only a 5 minutes walk to LKF and all of Hong Kong's CBD.With convenient access to MTR and major bus and tram lines.
space: The apartment is a well appointed studio that fits 2 people comfortably, any more people than that and I make no guarantees to your comfort level. There's a large kitchen with all the basics and a large, modern bathroom (a rarity in Hong Kong.) There's a lot of storage, a very big closet with enough space for all your clothes and more. SoHo and the neighboring Sheung Wan are thriving communities with an eclectic array of restaurants, coffee shops and boutiques from local owners. And it's just a few minutes to all the large stores on Queen's Road and IFC. In my opinion, it really has it all.

neighborhood_overview: SoHo consists of restaurants, bars, nightclubs, art galleries and antique stores of Staunton Street and Elgin Street. The  area has a rich contrast between past and present and makes for great sightseeing on foot. This district treads a precarious balance between preserving the Chinese and colonial cultures that shaped it, and recent modern developments.
transit: Catching a cab is easy 1 block down on Hollywood Road,  the MTR is just a short walk down the hill next to trams and buses. The Airport Express that takes you to and from Hong Kong International Airport is only a 10 minute walk away and when arriving, you can catch a ride up the Central/Mid-Levels Covered Escalator that will take you right to the door of the apartment.
access: The guest has access to everything in the apartment, during your stay, it's your home and I want you to feel comfortable and do as you please.
interaction: My interaction with you will be minimal. I will be on hand to give you the keys and to show you  around the unit a little and then again when you're ready to check out. Other than that, I will be out of your hair the rest of your stay. Of course, if you need my assistance for anything, I am always available.
house_rules: For the duration of your stay, this is your home, you are welcome to treat it as such. You are welcome to do what you like but I ask that, like your own home, you treat it with respect. If anything gets broken or has any lasting damage, all I ask that you let me know. The same goes if you plan to take something from the apartment, just let me know, I'm sure we can come to an arrangement. Other than that you are free to do as you like and act how you would in your own home. I wholly encourage pets of all shapes and sizes as long as their owners are caring and responsible with them  As for smoking, there's an ash tray that gets cleaned out every day, in the stairwell right by the elevator. If you just have to smoke inside the unit, please leave a window open. And never ever smoke in bed, but that is more a rule of life than for this house.

host_about:
I am an entrepreneur in Hong Kong, a co-founder of a start-up company in FinTech. 

I got my Master degree (Chemical engineering) in the United States and bachelor degree in China mainland. After graduate, I worked one year in United States, and then came back to Shanghai and work as a senior R&D Engineer in a world's fortune 500 company. 

I love science and math, and also love travelling and hosting! In my spare time, I host guests with extra apartments. I am happy to make friends with guests from all over the world. 

My apartments are located in Sheung Wan and Central area, which is the best spot for travelers in Hong Kong Island! It is just walk distance of 2 minutes to Sheung Wan MTR, 1 min to bus stop, 5 min to ferry, 10 min to Lan Kwai Fong and SOHO area (elevator to mid-level)! They are also very quiet compared with general big city accommodations, because they face the quiet and small streets and, so there is no need to worry about big city noise and just enjoy you night time and good sleep! The price is also unbeatable compared with the other flats in the same location.

Located only 1 minute walk from exit A, Jordan Station
 
We are a stylish hostel located in the heart of Kowloon Peninsula, in the famous shopping and commercial area of Jordan district.  Only 1 minutes’ walk from the Jordan MTR Station and walking distance to various attractions like the Jade Market and Temple Street Night Market, the hotel’s location gives our clients easy access to other parts of the Kowloon Peninsula and Hong Kong Island, whether you are here for business or leisure, this is where your home is away from home.

Our management team strives for offering good value for our guests.  We believes that “Good things come in small packages, simplicity is the real philosophy of sophistication”. At the same time, with our “Best friend attitude”, we aim at treating every guest as our best friend and make their stay a memorable one.  Deluxe Family Suite is our new concept of room category making family travel a much more affordable one than ever before.

Super Mini Room without window
Up to  10 square meter ,These rooms are smartly designed for offering maximum comfortability, they are also equipped with high quality beds and beddings and dockings for recharging electronic devices.

Standard Single Room without window
Up to  12 square meter ,These rooms are smartly designed for offering maximum comfortability, they are also equipped with high quality beds and beddings and dockings for recharging electronic devices.

Deluxe Room
Up to 18 square meter ,Furnished with designer décor and modern lighting, these rooms provide a real home away from home after a long day of work or discovery of the city.  Guests can have choices of one double bed (16 square meter) or two single beds (18 square meter).

4-beds Room without window
Up to 16 square meter ,Equipped with 2 bunk bed, these rooms make family travel a much more affordable one.

Family Room
Up to 22 square meter ,Equipped with a double bed and a bunk bed, these rooms make family travel a much more affordable one.

Pandora Suite
Up to 30 square meter ,Each Pandora Suite comprises of a living room with sofa and TV set, and a bedroom equipped with double bed and a bunk bed.  These rooms can comfortably accommodate a family of four.

Executive Room
Up to 26 square meter ,These rooms are elegantly designed to meet the requirements of both business and leisure travellers.  They are perfect for those guests who are looking for high quality of standards in a more spacious room.
the quickest way from the airport to our serviced hotel would be taking airport express to Kowloon station (around hkd90 per head, 25 mins) and change Taxi (around hkd25-30) to our hotel (Buckingham building). 
alternatively , the most economical way is to take shuttle bus A22 and get off at 4th stop, Chi Wo Street, Jordan Road   (around hkd40 per head, one hour)

host_about:
Hi everyone!

My name is Mike and I am an expatriate living in Hong Kong. I am a fun loving and easy going person who loves to read, play badminton and travel. I have been fortunate to have traveled to several cities in US, Europe, Australia and Asia. Personally I love making new friends, engaging in diversity and learning about new cultures. I am honored to live in such a multi-cultural, vibrant and enjoyable city and I am extremely excited to have the opportunity to host guests from all over the world.

So come down - have a great trip and I look forward to being your host!

You may come out of Exit B5, take the footbridge to Man Sing Street and walk north to Man Yuen Street. Or you may come out of Exit A, take the tunnel to Jordan Road/Ferry Street and walk north on Ferry Street to Man Yuen Street (look for Vanguard supermarket). The MTR will take you most places you wish to go. You may purchase single-journey tickets or an Octopus card for convenient local travel.  Bus: There is a bus stop on Ferry Street between Man Yuen Street and Man Ying Street. Buses to Tsim Sha Tsui depart from here. You may also take the MTR. Note that buses require exact change or Octopus payment. Taxi: There are plenty of taxis in this area. Flagfall is currently HK22. The best combination of great value and proximity to all the touristic locations.  -Canton Road (5 min walk): The most famous shopping area in Hong Kong where you can find all the worlds famous brands. host_about:
Hello everyone on Airbnb! My goal is to have my footprints in all the countries in the world. (How big a goal it is!) I have been to Australia, the UK, Italy, France, Monaco, Holland and Korea for travelling, and to the US, China, Taiwan, Singapore, Malaysia, Indonesia, Thailand and Cambodia mainly for work. I lived in China, Thailand and Mexico for years and now living in my hometown Hong Kong. I enjoy every single moment travelling from one place to another. It's the best time for me to overlook the world and to empty my mind. It is said that the world is becoming smaller and smaller. We are on the southern hemisphere in the morning and appear on the northern in just some hours. The best way for me to feel home anywhere is to meet local people! I listen to their stories and learn their cultures, respect their traditions and share mine with them. This is what travelling means to me.

Thanks to Airbnb, it provides a platform for people to meet friends and look for accommodation at reasonable price. Star-rated hotels are great, but local hosts can give you warm welcome and make you feel home.

I have years of experience hosting foreign guests through couhcsrufnig (CS), but stopped hosting since 2 years ago. After I returned from Mexico to Hong Kong in 2014 to start this hotel business, I found that airbnb is one of the best platforms which combines couhcsrufnig and business into one. Look forward to seeing you, my new friend!

host_about:
Hi everyone!

My name is Mike and I am an expatriate living in Hong Kong. I am a fun loving and easy going person who loves to read, play badminton and travel. I have been fortunate to have traveled to several cities in US, Europe, Australia and Asia. Personally I love making new friends, engaging in diversity and learning about new cultures. I am honored to live in such a multi-cultural, vibrant and enjoyable city and I am extremely excited to have the opportunity to host guests from all over the world.

So come down - have a great trip and I look forward to being your host!

neighborhood_overview: By far the best neighbourhood in Hong Kong, PoHo has all the convenience of nearby Central and SoHo without the noise. It really is a hidden gem full of quiet green gardens and parks with trees shading the streets that are lined with traditional printing presses and antique shops sitting beside contemporary art galleries, designer stores, cafés, restaurants and bars. Historical buildings are around every corner and tourist trails criss-cross the lanes immersing you in the history of the area. Children from the local schools playing games and the elderly residents practising tai chi also provide a real sense of community.
transit: Two MTR stations (Sheung Wan and Sai Ying Pun), both within 10 minutes walk from the apartment provide easy access to both the neighbourhood and beyond. Taxis are abundant along both Bonham Road and Hollywood Road.

neighborhood_overview: Highly urban and dense so everything you need for daily life is within a 5-minute walk.  Safe all the time.  Busiest during the day but a short walk from nightlife.  Home to lots of young professionals. 5-minute walk to lots of art galleries, bars, restaurants, coffee shops. 10-minute walk to one of the best Western-style supermarkets in Hong Kong.
notes: If you dislike anything it will likely be the shower situation and the overall apartment size, both of which are common in less expensive Hong Kong apartments: No separate shower stall and you need to flip a switch to heat up the shower's water in advance. Water stays hot for about 5 minutes, so I always turn it on and off throughout each shower to maintain the heat. Apartment is 150 square feet/14 square meters but it feels bigger due to efficient layout. In security features, the building has a 24-hour onsite security guard and an iron front gate that locks at night. ***The cleaning fee includes the cost of laundering winter bedding.***
transit: Transportation is this apartment's selling point. You can easily access all of Hong Kong and Macau with minimal transfers. 20-minute walk to either Central (downtown) or Hong Kong University 3-minute walk to MTR (subway) Sai Ying Pun stop 10-minute walk to Macau Ferry terminal Tram (streetcar), tons of buses and taxis take you everywhere else.

house_rules: Please minimize loud noises or music in the apartment between 10 p.m. and 8 a.m. out of respect for my neighbors.  Please no smoking, pets or young children.
host_about:
I tend to go big or go home with everything I do including vacation. I'm an independent, adventurous traveler whose ideal vacation is either very urban and packed full of art, food and nightlife or very rural, outdoorsy and relaxing.

As a host, because my only listing is the tiny yet well located apartment I live in, I rent it out only when I'm out of town. My friend who is native bilingual in Mandarin and English and lives and works a short walk away is your onsite contact, but I'm happy to message you before and during your stay. I strive to, from afar, make my apartment easy to get to and stay at. 

My life motto is the chorus of the musical Caberet's title song:
What good is sitting alone in your room?
Come here the music play.
Life is a cabaret, old chum!
Come to the cabaret.

summary: 舍位於九龍尖沙咀中心區金馬倫道 29樓及柯士甸路18 号大廈旁就有港鐵尖沙咀站B2出口及佐敦站D出囗,來回直達機場的A21機場巴士站,更有來回機場快線。酒店附近觀光旅遊景點豐富,步行約十分鐘便到達香港文化中心、海港城名店區、維多利亞港、天星碼頭、名人手印星光大道及中港碼頭等。 到中國大陸或澳門也十分方便。大廈門口便可乘撘各種交通公具如機場巴士、市內巴士、的士、地鐵、小巴等。交通四通八達。穿梭香港九龍辦事、購物、探親、觀光都非常方便。 舍 由於地理位置優越,各式商店及各國食品餐廳、銀行、找換店、便利店等生活設施齊備,一應俱全,絕對是賓客來體驗不一样的香港住宿文化,最新最潮的LOFT民宿享受,最新潮力。 酒店全新裝修,房間裝修型格時尚,並每天進行清潔消毒,更採用一次性床上用品務求讓旅客睡得更舒適、更安心整潔,此非一般尖沙咀破舊小賓館可比。 於2014年 冬季全新開業的精品酒店,位於尖沙咀區樞紐,坐落商業、購物及娛樂的心臟地帶。毗鄰世界知名的維多利亞港等多個名勝地標及大型購物中心。酒店位於港鐵尖沙咀站上蓋,前往中國大陸只需四十分鐘,距離火車站天星碼頭及中港客運碼頭更是瞬步之遙。乘坐機場快線列車或計程車來往香港國際機場,車程亦只須四十分鐘。 獨立洗手間 LCD電視 獨立空調 24小時冷熱水浴室 免費無線寬頻上網 風筒及電熱瓶 浴巾及衛生用品房間設施齊全。床頭櫃、獨立電源、USB 插頭。每房間具獨立洗手間和24小時冷熱水浴室、電熱瓶、房內WiFi寬頻上網和獨立空調。更為旅客提供方便的服務如提供一次性床上用品及曰常用品毛巾、拖鞋、另備有男仕日用品。

summary: Located in Mid-Levels, close to the world longest escalators and walking distance from SOHO and LKF. Very bright inside with breathtaking view on Hong Kong and the bay! We love our furnitures from Indonesia in the living room.
space: Actually, there is bedrooms and one playroom. One of the bedroom has bank beds and a baby cot. The other one ha a queen size bed. In the playroom, when we receive guests, we add two mattresses on the play mat. It's still comfortable. You won't have access to the main cupboards are they are already full of our clothes and stuffs. It is a non smokers apartment. Our home is kids friendly as we have a playroom and a little table in the living room too. Of course, we ask our young guests to be very cautious with children books and other games they can use. Our apartment is quiet. No big works just near to it. no noise from the neighbours .

neighborhood_overview: We live in Hong kong island. neighborhood_overview: Sham Shui Po is an interesting place.  You will see the authentic Hong Kong while you live here.  This is a place that the Tourism Board seldom introduce but it is a special experience living here.  It is not occupied by chain stores and brand names.  Things are cheap and stores and hawkers are operated by the owner themselves and this means more human interactions. The Ap Liu Street, for example, is famous for electronic products and second-hand products, while the Golden Shopping Center for computer products.  Ladies will find the Pei Ho Street area interesting as there are clothes and fashion accessories selling at cheap prices. And of course there are local delicacies.
notes: The calendar is correct.  It is what-you-see-is-what-you-get. For bookings of less than 3 nights please do within one week. I will not agree to any invitation to deal without going through the system, and also no bargain please. For an exchange arrangement please ask.
transit: The place is close to MTR stations.  There are bus stops downstairs taking you to many places.  I especially recommend the bus no. 2 which goes to Tsim Sha Tsui Ferry Pier.  Try the ice-cream car and take ferry to the island side.  The Victoria Harbor view is great, and is different during the day and the night.  Bus no. 2 will pass through Price Edward, Mongkok, Jordan and you can visit these places too.  Get off at Jordan to the Temple Street at night, have dinner there, have fun.

neighborhood_overview: Made internationally famous by the 1960 film The World of Suzie Wong, historic Wan Chai is not just Hong Kong’s party district; by day it’s a pleasant neighbourhood for wandering and shopping. Dotted along Queen's Road East are a number of excellent rattan and Chinese furniture shops that will happily arrange to have your purchases sent home for you or, for competitively priced clothing, try Spring Garden Lane where stalls offload garments originally earmarked for export. Techies won’t complain about getting lost in the Wanchai Computer Centre on Hennessy Road; a building jam-packed with hardware, software, accessories and other gadgets. And both kids and ‘kidults’ might want to check out Tai Yuen Street; an entire strip of toys touting everything from the latest to the classics.

Due to the reason that Sep-Apr is peak season, you are advised to make your reservation earlier.   I can only do first book first serve basis, where I won't cancel current booking just because other guests have a longer / bigger booking.  Due to strict cancellation policy, I haven't got any booking cancellation so far).

Max Capacity is cater to big group consists of family n kids with standard asian size.  If group with members with huge body size or some members prefer to have a solid bed by their own, not sharing with other, then please split your group into two apartments for more comfortable stay.  I have tried my best to write the apartment description as detail as I could. Please spend time to read through before you book.  I am definitely happy to answer any question that is not in the apartment description.

Thank you and have a nice day.

I am so glad many of you appreciate all the hard work and bare with the occasionally 1% silly mistake / fault / defect I have made.  Thank you so much for your patient.

For Pricing, at the listing page, enter check in date, check out date and total number of guests.  The system will auto generate the price for your consideration.  Regarding the currency display, it depends on your own setting, you can change your currency setting at the lower left panel of your airbnb page under the "LANGUAGE", you will see "CURRENCY" setting.  Just click on it to change to any currency that you wish to display.

The listing page only able to display DEFAULT DAILY, WEEKLY and MONTHLY rate that only applies to dates that I did not input any VARIABLE price.  FYI, I will normally enter the VARIABLE price 6 to 8 months ahead.  For example, MAR, I will UPDATE variable price for OCT - DEC end of the year, JUN I will UPDATE variable price MAR next year (especially 3rd and 4th week of MAR is always FULL HOUSE due to Ruby Seven Event), and  JAN, I will UPDATE variable price for JUN-SEPT etc.  So if now is DEC 2014, if you book next year DEC 2015, for sure you will get default rate serving as EARLY BIRD discount.

The Weekly price (10% discount from daily rate) applies for booking over 7 nights only and Monthly price (20% discount from daily rate)  applies for booking 28 nights or more. The Additional Guests Fee applies to all booking at daily/weekly/monthly rate (US10-30 per night per guest beyond 1-3 guests depends on the size & number of room of each listing). The Additional Guest Fee covers extra cleaning/extra mattress setting/clean sheet/clean towel/extra electricity/water, extra wear and tear incurred.  The Cleaning Fee charges cover cleaning before and after your stay.  For Extra Cleaning during your stay, General House-Keeping is HK80 per hour.  If you want FULL CLEANING that included new sheets and towel replacement would the same with the Initial Cleaning Fee per visit.

neighborhood_overview: Made internationally famous by the 1960 film The World of Suzie Wong, historic Wan Chai is not just Hong Kong’s party district; by day it’s a pleasant neighbourhood for wandering and shopping. Dotted along Queen's Road East are a number of excellent rattan and Chinese furniture shops that will happily arrange to have your purchases sent home for you or, for competitively priced clothing, try Spring Garden Lane where stalls offload garments originally earmarked for export. Techies won’t complain about getting lost in the Wanchai Computer Centre on Hennessy Road; a building jam-packed with hardware, software, accessories and other gadgets. And both kids and ‘kidults’ might want to check out Tai Yuen Street; an entire strip of toys touting everything from the latest to the classics.
